          <div class="doc-section">
            <h3 id="content-guidelines" class="doc-h3">Content Guidelines<span class="h3-badge" style="background:rgba(37,99,235,0.1);color:var(--prism-violet);">Recommended</span></h3>
            <div class="do-dont-grid">
              <div class="do-card"><span class="card-label">Do</span><ul>
                <li>Set Length to match the actual code length sent to the user.</li>
                <li>Display the Error state + helper text immediately on incorrect code.</li>
                <li>Use <code style="font-family:monospace;font-size:13px;padding:2px 8px;border-radius:6px;background:rgba(37,99,235,0.06);color:var(--prism-violet);">autocomplete="one-time-code"</code> for SMS autofill.</li>
                <li>Show a clear helper text (e.g. "Code sent to +91 &#8226;&#8226;&#8226;&#8226;&#8226;&#8226;7890").</li>
                <li>Clear all boxes and show Error state on wrong code.</li>
              </ul></div>
              <div class="dont-card"><span class="card-label">Don't</span><ul>
                <li>Show a 6-box OTP for a 4-digit code &#8212; mismatched lengths confuse users.</li>
                <li>Only reveal errors after the user submits the full form.</li>
                <li>Disable paste &#8212; it frustrates users switching from SMS.</li>
                <li>Leave the helper row empty &#8212; context reduces re-send rates.</li>
                <li>Keep entered digits in Error state without clearing.</li>
              </ul></div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

