          <div class="doc-section">
            <h2 id="alignment-placement" class="doc-section-title">Alignment &amp; Placement</h2>
            <p class="doc-section-subtitle">Consistent placement ensures the OTP Input is predictable and easy to locate.</p>
            <ul class="doc-list">
              <li><strong>Login / verification pages:</strong> Center the OTP Input horizontally on the page for a focused, hero-style placement.</li>
              <li><strong>Inline forms:</strong> Left-align the OTP Input with other form fields for visual consistency.</li>
              <li><strong>Mobile:</strong> Use Large size for comfortable touch targets. Center on screen for single-purpose verification flows.</li>
              <li><strong>RTL layouts:</strong> Set <code style="font-family:monospace;font-size:13px;padding:2px 8px;border-radius:6px;background:rgba(37,99,235,0.06);color:var(--prism-violet);">dir="rtl"</code> on the wrapper and let the browser handle visual mirroring. Do not reorder DOM inputs.</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <hr class="doc-divider"/>

          <div class="doc-section">
            <h2 id="detailed-guidelines" class="doc-section-title">Complete Do's and Don'ts</h2>
            <p class="doc-section-subtitle">Guidelines for effective OTP Input usage.</p>
            <div class="do-dont-grid">
              <div class="do-card"><span class="card-label">Do</span><ul>
                <li><strong>Match length to code:</strong> Set Length to match the actual code length sent to the user.</li>
                <li><strong>Immediate error feedback:</strong> Display the Error state + helper text immediately on incorrect code.</li>
                <li><strong>Enable SMS autofill:</strong> Use <code style="font-family:monospace;font-size:13px;padding:2px 8px;border-radius:6px;background:rgba(37,99,235,0.06);color:var(--prism-violet);">autocomplete="one-time-code"</code> for SMS autofill.</li>
                <li><strong>Show context:</strong> Show a clear helper text (e.g. "Code sent to +91 &#8226;&#8226;&#8226;&#8226;&#8226;&#8226;7890").</li>
                <li><strong>Use Show Label=OFF only</strong> when the label is already provided by surrounding page content.</li>
                <li><strong>Clear on error:</strong> Clear all boxes and show Error state on wrong code &#8212; users should re-enter cleanly.</li>
              </ul></div>
              <div class="dont-card"><span class="card-label">Don't</span><ul>
                <li><strong>Mismatched length:</strong> Show a 6-box OTP for a 4-digit code &#8212; mismatched lengths confuse users.</li>
                <li><strong>Delayed errors:</strong> Only reveal errors after the user submits the full form.</li>
                <li><strong>Block paste:</strong> Disable paste &#8212; it frustrates users switching from SMS.</li>
                <li><strong>Empty helpers:</strong> Leave the helper row empty &#8212; context reduces re-send rates.</li>
                <li><strong>Hidden label without context:</strong> Hide the label without another visible indication of what the field expects.</li>
                <li><strong>Stale error digits:</strong> Keep entered digits in Error state without clearing.</li>
              </ul></div>
            </div>
          </div>

