          <div class="doc-section">
            <h3 id="rtl-support" class="doc-h3">RTL Support</h3>
            <ul class="doc-list">
              <li><strong>Wrapper direction:</strong> Set <code style="font-family:monospace;font-size:13px;padding:2px 8px;border-radius:6px;background:rgba(37,99,235,0.06);color:var(--prism-violet);">dir="rtl"</code> on the wrapper element. The browser handles visual mirroring of the flex layout.</li>
              <li><strong>Do not reorder DOM:</strong> Inputs remain in DOM order (1&#8594;4 or 1&#8594;6). The <code style="font-family:monospace;font-size:13px;padding:2px 8px;border-radius:6px;background:rgba(37,99,235,0.06);color:var(--prism-violet);">dir="rtl"</code> attribute reverses the visual display.</li>
              <li><strong>Arabic labels:</strong> RTL variants use Arabic label text (<code style="font-family:monospace;font-size:13px;padding:2px 8px;border-radius:6px;background:rgba(37,99,235,0.06);color:var(--prism-violet);">&#x631;&#x645;&#x632; &#x627;&#x644;&#x62A;&#x62D;&#x642;&#x642;</code>) and right-aligned helper text.</li>
              <li><strong>Keyboard navigation:</strong> Arrow keys follow visual direction &#8212; ArrowRight moves to the visually right box (which is the previous input in DOM order).</li>
            </ul>
