          <h2 id="accessibility" class="doc-section-title">Accessibility</h2>
          <p class="doc-section-subtitle">Guidelines for ensuring OTP Input is accessible across assistive technologies and input methods.</p>

          <div class="doc-section">
            <h3 id="keyboard-interaction" class="doc-h3">Keyboard Interaction</h3>
            <table class="size-table">
              <thead><tr><th>Action</th><th>Result</th></tr></thead>
              <tbody>
                <tr><td><code>Numeric key (0&#8211;9)</code></td><td>Enters digit in focused box and auto-advances focus to next box.</td></tr>
                <tr><td><code>Backspace</code> on filled box</td><td>Clears digit, stays on current box.</td></tr>
                <tr><td><code>Backspace</code> on empty box</td><td>Moves focus to previous box.</td></tr>
                <tr><td><code>Tab</code></td><td>Moves focus to next box.</td></tr>
                <tr><td><code>Shift+Tab</code></td><td>Moves focus to previous box.</td></tr>
                <tr><td>Paste (full code)</td><td>Distributes pasted digits across all boxes from the focused position.</td></tr>
                <tr><td><code>ArrowLeft</code> / <code>ArrowRight</code></td><td>Moves focus to adjacent box.</td></tr>
              </tbody>
            </table>
            <div style="margin-top:16px;padding:16px 20px;background:rgba(37,99,235,0.05);border:1px solid rgba(37,99,235,0.15);border-radius:12px;">
              <p style="font-size:14px;color:var(--prism-text);line-height:1.6;margin:0;">Auto-advance on input must not trap keyboard users; <code style="font-family:monospace;font-size:13px;padding:2px 8px;border-radius:6px;background:rgba(37,99,235,0.06);color:var(--prism-violet);">Tab</code> must still work as expected to move focus out of the OTP group.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

