          <div class="doc-section">
            <h3 id="aria-attributes-screen-reader-guidance" class="doc-h3">ARIA Attributes &amp; Screen Reader Guidance</h3>
            <ul class="doc-list">
              <li><strong>Group label:</strong> Wrap all digit inputs in a <code style="font-family:monospace;font-size:13px;padding:2px 8px;border-radius:6px;background:rgba(37,99,235,0.06);color:var(--prism-violet);">&lt;fieldset&gt;</code> with a <code style="font-family:monospace;font-size:13px;padding:2px 8px;border-radius:6px;background:rgba(37,99,235,0.06);color:var(--prism-violet);">&lt;legend&gt;</code> matching the label text.</li>
              <li><strong>Per-input label:</strong> Each <code style="font-family:monospace;font-size:13px;padding:2px 8px;border-radius:6px;background:rgba(37,99,235,0.06);color:var(--prism-violet);">&lt;input&gt;</code> must have <code style="font-family:monospace;font-size:13px;padding:2px 8px;border-radius:6px;background:rgba(37,99,235,0.06);color:var(--prism-violet);">aria-label="Digit N of M"</code> (e.g. "Digit 1 of 4").</li>
              <li><strong>Error announcement:</strong> When Error state activates, update an <code style="font-family:monospace;font-size:13px;padding:2px 8px;border-radius:6px;background:rgba(37,99,235,0.06);color:var(--prism-violet);">aria-live="assertive"</code> region with the error message.</li>
              <li><strong>Helper text association:</strong> Associate the helper text with the group using <code style="font-family:monospace;font-size:13px;padding:2px 8px;border-radius:6px;background:rgba(37,99,235,0.06);color:var(--prism-violet);">aria-describedby</code> on the <code style="font-family:monospace;font-size:13px;padding:2px 8px;border-radius:6px;background:rgba(37,99,235,0.06);color:var(--prism-violet);">&lt;fieldset&gt;</code>.</li>
              <li><strong>Disabled:</strong> Disabled inputs must have the <code style="font-family:monospace;font-size:13px;padding:2px 8px;border-radius:6px;background:rgba(37,99,235,0.06);color:var(--prism-violet);">disabled</code> attribute, not just visual styling.</li>
              <li><strong>Mobile autofill:</strong> <code style="font-family:monospace;font-size:13px;padding:2px 8px;border-radius:6px;background:rgba(37,99,235,0.06);color:var(--prism-violet);">autocomplete="one-time-code"</code> enables OS-level SMS autofill without ARIA intervention.</li>
              <li><strong>Screen reader paste:</strong> Ensure paste events reflect the result back through value changes the screen reader can detect.</li>
              <li><strong>RTL:</strong> Set <code style="font-family:monospace;font-size:13px;padding:2px 8px;border-radius:6px;background:rgba(37,99,235,0.06);color:var(--prism-violet);">dir="rtl"</code> on the wrapper; do not reorder DOM inputs.</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

